  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strenghtening compliance and effective implementation of laws to support female victims in Colombia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Although in Colombia Laws 1257 and 1719 give a solid framework to advance women&#x2019;s rights and protection, the reality is that implementation remains weak and ineffectual. Sisma&#x2019;s experience in providing counselling and accompaniment to female survivors in recent years has shown a clear and persistent pattern of either a lack of awareness of these laws or a failure to comply with their measures. The laws to protect women and girls exist on paper, but in practice the majority of women are being failed by the system. Therefore, Sisma Mujer will be legally representing women who have survived sexual violence in 15 strategically chosen cases, with the aim of bringing them justice. If successful, this litigation work could create favourable jurisprudence that will help address the general problem of impunity, which could go on to help other women and girls in similar circumstances.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of legal and psychosocial support to women in 15 cases of violence. Activation of 15 protection mechanisms in those cases. Wider counselling services, support and legal advice to other female victims of violence. Establishment of self-group for women victims of intra-familial violence. To set legal precedents tat will benefit other women and girls. Monitoring, follow.up and advocacy regarding compliance with Laws 1257 and 1719. To identify, challenge and publicly advocate against draft bills and reforms in Congress which negatively impact on the protective provisions of Laws 1257 and 1719 and women&#x2019;s right to a life free from violence. Production and dissemination of a report monitoring compliance with Laws 1257 and 1719 including recommendations for strengthening compliance. Active participation in public debate around issues relating to sexual and gender-based violence</narrative>
  </description>
